	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=567&mid=10394562733626>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=567&mid=10394562733626>RE: How hard does this hit for?</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=567&mid=10394562733626#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Dec 9th 1:15 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=92334><span id=Sage>Morigu</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>192 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It works for all melee classes, INCLUDING warriors who can use the above weapon. The damage calculation for a single hits the same no matter who you are.<br><br>The main difference's between classes is more on how often you hit, example how often you double attack, or duel wield successfully with your second hand. Your question was how hard does this hit for, if you don't feel like reading, here it is(unless they have changed it lately it should be still true):<br><br>Modal Damage:<br>------------<br>(VERY SLOW) IF WeaponDelay &gt; 42<br>1.) DamageBonus = One Handed DamageBonus + ((Level - 27) / 4) + (WeaponDelay - 34) / 3<br><br>2.) PrimaryModal = WeaponDamage * 2 + DamageBonus<br><br>Maximum Damage:<br>--------------<br>(VERY SLOW) IF WeaponDelay &gt; 42<br>1.) DamageBonus = One Handed DamageBonus + ((Level - 27) / 4) + (WeaponDelay - 34) / 3<br><br>2.) MaximumDamage = WeaponDamage * ((Strength + WeaponSkill) / 100) + DamageBonus</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Sensei Jhereg, 65th Monk, &lt;Celestial Navigators&gt;, Vazaelle<br>Vanidor Silverbranch, 40th Wizard, &lt;Celestial Navigators&gt;, Vazaelle</td></tr>
